  <h1>Take Action</h1>
  <p>
    Stopping ambulance balance billing will take voices from across the country.
    You can make a real impact — even with small actions.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Share your story</h2>
  <p>
    If you or someone you know has received a surprise ambulance bill, your experience matters.
    These stories help illustrate how widespread and harmful the problem is.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:onojk123@gmail.com?subject=My%20ambulance%20billing%20story">
      Send your experience →
    </a>
  </p>

  <h2>2. Contribute research or insights</h2>
  <p>
    Policy researchers, health economists, EMTs, medical billing experts, and data analysts are invited to collaborate.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="mailto:onojk123@gmail.com?subject=Collaboration%20or%20research%20idea">
      Start a collaboration →
    </a>
  </p>

  <h2>3. Spread awareness</h2>
  <p>
    Share facts, link to the site, and tell people the truth:
    <strong>Ground ambulance billing is the last major loophole in U.S. emergency care.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>4. Contact your representatives</h2>
  <p>
    Encourage lawmakers to support a national ban on ambulance balance billing.
    Ground ambulances must be included under federal surprise billing protections.
  </p>

  <p>More tools and ready-to-send templates will be added here as the campaign evolves.</p>
